cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify personality traits through essays. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of SVM classifiers, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve statistical analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with affective computing, which falls under the sub-category cs.CY (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics). Finally, the paper involves the use of features to identify personality traits, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
